```
Criminal Facts
Case Number: 2022고단1009
The defendant, upon seeing a post about a "high-paying part-time job" on Facebook around April 2022, contacted an unidentified person and agreed to post items for sale on second-hand trading websites and other platforms without the intention or ability to sell any items. They planned to deceive buyers into paying for these non-existent items. The unidentified person was responsible for posting the fraudulent sales posts online, while the defendant was responsible for opening a bank account in their name to withdraw and hand over the money transferred by the victims.
On or around April 25, 2022, the unidentified person accessed the game 'C' by Company B from an unknown location and created a false post stating, "Selling D (game money)”. They lied to the victim E, who contacted them after seeing the post, stating, "I will sell 20.7 billion D for 538,200 won."
However, in reality, both the defendant and the unidentified person had neither the intention nor the ability to sell any items or game money, even after receiving money from the victims.
Despite this, the defendant, in conspiracy with the unidentified person, deceived the victims and received a total of 28,808,300 won in 99 transactions, including 538,200 won transferred to the defendant's F bank account (account number omitted) around 16:39 on the same day, from April 25, 2022, to May 16, 2022, as listed in the attached crime summary table 1.
Thus, the defendant, in conspiracy with the unidentified person, defrauded the victims and misappropriated their property.

Case Number: 2022고단1652
The defendant, upon seeing a post about a "high-paying part-time job" on Facebook around April 2022, contacted an unidentified person and agreed to post items for sale on second-hand trading websites and other platforms without the intention or ability to sell any items. They planned to deceive buyers into paying for these non-existent items. The unidentified person was responsible for posting the fraudulent sales posts online, while the defendant was responsible for opening a bank account in their name to withdraw and hand over the money transferred by the victims.
On or around April 25, 2022, the unidentified person, after seeing a post in a KakaoTalk open chat room posted by victim G, contacted the victim and lied, saying, "I will sell 12 billion D (game money used in Company B's game C) for 336,000 won in cash."
However, in reality, both the defendant and the unidentified person had neither the intention nor the ability to sell any game money, even after receiving money from the victims.
The defendant, in conspiracy with the unidentified person, deceived the victims and received a total of 15,790,700 won in 46 transactions, including 336,000 won transferred to the defendant's F bank account (account number omitted) around 18:48 on the same day, from April 25, 2022, to May 17, 2022, as listed in the attached crime summary table 2.
Thus, the defendant, in conspiracy with the unidentified person, defrauded the victims and misappropriated their property.

target_reason: Explanation: w00011 argues that an actor with awareness of a crime actively contributes to the success of that crime, but this fails to provide sufficient logical basis to prove a direct connection between the existence of criminal consciousness and the defendant's active contribution. Just because there is a consciousness of crime does not necessarily mean that active contribution follows, which is merely an assumption. Therefore, this argument shows weakness in terms of direct relevance to the criminal facts and logical validity. For these reasons, w00011 is considered the weakest argument element.
